Rundeck is an open-source automation platform designed to help manage and streamline IT operations, especially in cloud or data center environments. It allows users to create, schedule, and run jobs that automate repetitive tasks, such as software deployments, system administration tasks, incident response, and more. Rundeck provides a web-based interface, API, and command-line tools for job management and execution, enabling teams to manage workflows, trigger tasks based on conditions, and control access to specific functions.

It integrates well with DevOps tools and can be customized for various use cases like managing infrastructure, automating cloud management, or handling incident responses.
